Proceeds of each sale under the Program will be sent to the shareholder in the form of a check (less the transaction fee). Sale requests under the Program will typically be combined with other sale requests received from Client shareholders and Shares will be submitted in bulk to an affiliated registered broker/dealer for sale. Shares will be sold under the Program generally within one business day of Agent’s receipt (on behalf of such banking affiliate) of the sale request, but in no event more than five business days (except where deferral is necessary under state or federal regulations). The price per Share received by the selling shareholder under the Program will equal the market price Agent (on behalf of such banking affiliate) receives for the Shares (or, if more than one bulk trade is executed on the day the Shares are sold, then the price per Share shall equal the weighted average market price received for all Shares sold that day).

OTHER SERVICES AND CHARGES
Shareholder Plan Enrollment: If Client has not designated a banking affiliate of Agent to manage a direct stock purchase or dividend reinvestment plan, the Client hereby authorizes and directs a banking affiliate of Agent to establish and administer a share liquidation program ("Program") under which registered shareholders may enroll book-entry Shares for liquidation according to the following terms and conditions. A transaction fee of $15.00 plus $0.12 per Share will be charged for each sale through the Program. Upon receiving a sale request from a registered shareholder, Agent (on behalf of the banking affiliate) will process the request via an affiliated broker/dealer. The proceeds from each sale under the Program will be disbursed to the shareholder in the form of a check (deducting the transaction fee). Sale requests will generally be grouped with other sale requests from Client's shareholders and submitted for bulk trade. Shares will typically be sold within one business day of receipt, but not more than five business days (except where deferral is necessary under state or federal regulations). The price per Share received by the selling shareholder under the Program will correspond to the market price Agent (on behalf of the banking affiliate) obtains for the Shares (or, if multiple bulk trades are executed on the day the Shares are sold, then the price per Share shall be the weighted average market price obtained for all Shares sold that day).
